description: This walk takes you from the village of Keld to the lovely viewpoint, old bridge and waterfall at Ravenseat in the Yorkshire Dales. Start the walk in the village and then cross to the other side of the River Swale near Catrake Force waterfall. You can then follow footpaths west past Currack Force and Wain Wath Force falls. The route continues past Cotterby Scar to How Edge before coming to Ravenseat. It's a lovely scenic spot with views of the Whistundale Beck, a picturesque old stone clapper bridge and some beautiful Swaledale countryside. There's also the photogenic Jenny Whalley Force waterfall to see in the area.

details.subtitle: Further Information and Other Local Ideas
details.content: To continue your walking in the area try the circular Keld Waterfalls Walk which visits some of the pretty waterfalls in the area. For more walking ideas in the area see the Yorkshire Dales Walks page.
